<TITLE> Iraq's Sadr militia to suspend armed actions: aide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BAGHDAD, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The Mehdi Army militia of Iraqi Shia cleric Moqtada al-Sadr will halt all "armed actions" after he ordered a suspension of its activities, a senior aide to the cleric said on Wednesday. Asked if the suspension order meant no attacks against US troops, the aide said: "All kinds of armed actions are to be frozen, without exception."
